Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getPinConstraint(25.10)                                getPinConstraint(25.10)

Name
       getPinConstraint  - Retrieves information about the constraints set for
       a partition pin or an I/O pin using the setPinConstraint command

Syntax
       getPinConstraint

       [-help]

       [-dictFile <string>]

       [[-global | -cell <cell_name>]

       [-global | -pin <pin_name_list>]]

       Retrieves information about the constraints set for a partition pin  or
       an  I/O pin using the setPinConstraint command.  It displays the infor-
       mation in a tabular format output report that includes constraints from
       other sources (top/bottom preferred  layer  and  NDR-rule  from  setAt-
       tibute,  reserved layer for partition, pin/net-group /guide constraints
       presence)) and segregates between user-defined, default, and  lef  val-
       ues.

Parameters
       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the module. The module name is not re-
              quired if the command is run on a top-level module. You can  use
              wildcards (*?) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -dictFile <string>
              Writes  the output of the command in the specified text file (in
              dictionary format).

              Data_type: string, optional

       -global
              Specifies to get global constraints.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each getPinConstraint parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

              man getPinConstraint

       -pin <pin_name_list>
              Specifies  the  name of the partition pin. You can use wildcards
              (*?) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The following command prints all the constraints set  for  the
                specified module.

                getPinConstraint -cell dtmf_chip

                The following result is displayed on the screen:

                Default Global Values:

                ----------------------

                Minimum pin-to-pin track spacing : 2

                Pin to corner distance : 5

                Template from tech LEF

                -----------------------------

                | Layer | width | depth |

                -----------------------------

                | 2 | 0.2800 | 0.2800 |

                | 3 | 0.2800 | 0.2800 |

                | 4 | 0.2800 | 0.2800 |

                | 5 | 0.2800 | 0.2800 |

                | 6 | 0.4400 | 0.4400 |

                -----------------------------

                Global Constraint:

                -------------------

                Constraint on partition dtmf_chip :

                ----------------------

                Partition reserved layers { 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 }

                --------------------------

                | Side | allowed layer |

                --------------------------

                | top | 2 4 6 |

                | left | 3 5 |

                | bottom | 2 4 6 |

                | right | 3 5 |

                --------------------------

